---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie policy" description="What cookies blog.oriz.in uses.">
  <header class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-12 pb-6 border-b border-neutral-800">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Blog</a> /
      <a href="/legal/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Legal</a> / Cookies
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Cookie policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 prose prose-invert">
    <p>
      blog.oriz.in uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get away with.
    </p>

    <h2>What we set</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Theme + accent</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> keys
        <code>oriz:theme</code> and <code>oriz:accent</code> remember your
        preference between visits. No tracking.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Auth session</strong> — when you sign in, Firebase Authentication
        sets cookies on <code>auth.oriz.in</code> so you stay logged in across
        every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site. These are first-party and essential.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Site-specific preferences</strong> — bookmarks and recently-viewed
        post lists are kept in <code>localStorage</code> on this site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile, bot
        management). These are essential for site availability.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Giscus / GitHub</strong> sets cookies if you sign in to comment.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (once approved) may set advertising
        cookies. The consent banner lets you opt out per-purpose.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Opting out</h2>
    <p>
      You can clear localStorage and cookies for any oriz domain from your
      browser's site-data settings. Theme and auth will reset to defaults.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
